    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Austin Waves leans heavily into high-floor leadoff men and favorable park factors, with **Jacob Wilson** leading the charge at a 74.08 efficiency score. **Wilson** benefits from a massive 10% boost in park favorability and an advantageous matchup against Cameron (L); his leadoff positioning maximizes his volume, making him our highest-rated start. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** earns a 73.05 score despite facing a tough arm in Lambert; the combination of a 16% park boost and the dynamic platoon advantage against the right-hander offsets the skill of the opposing pitcher, keeping him in the elite tier of our daily rotation. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a cornerstone at 71.02, as his strong xwOBA profile and high-leverage order spot continue to drive value even against a solid arm like Ober.\n\nThe bench decision process was most difficult regarding **Coby Mayo**, who finished at 39.83, narrowly missing our 40-point \"Below Floor\" threshold. While **Mayo** gains significant value from the same park factors boosting **Gunnar Henderson**, his projected spot at the bottom of the order and the platoon disadvantage against Lambert ultimately lowered his efficiency below the cutoff. Meanwhile, we remain in a holding pattern with **Luis Robert Jr.** on the IL, and lack meaningful contributions today from **Kyle Tucker** and **Jackson Merrill** due to team off-days. With **Nasim Nunez** (47.72) and **Heliot Ramos** (48.04) rounding out the active roster, we are prioritizing their sprint speed and stolen base potential\u2014the scarcest commodities in our league\u2014to mitigate the risk posed by elite arms like Peralta and S\u00e1nchez. \n\nInvestors should monitor the status of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, as his lineup position remains pending; any shift toward the lower half of the order would necessitate a re-evaluation of his current 71.02 score. Furthermore, while **Nasim Nunez** presents a lower efficiency score, his matchup against a pitcher with a slow delivery provides an isolated boost to his stolen base probability, justifying his inclusion over other bench options despite the marginal raw output. We are effectively betting on the speed profiles of **Nasim Nunez**, **Jacob Wilson**, and **Heliot Ramos** to provide the necessary category velocity to support the power production expected from **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Gunnar Henderson**.",
